12 Amend the bill by striking out all of sections 4 and 5 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 4. 7 MRSA §3923-A, first ¶, as amended by PL 2013, c. 115, §10, is further
14 amended to read:
15 Except as provided in subsection 3 and section 3923‑C 3932-B, a dog owner or keeper
16 obtaining a license from a municipal clerk, dog licensing agent or dog recorder shall pay
17 the license and recording fees established in this section. For purposes of this section, "dog
18 licensing agent" means an animal shelter or a veterinarian pursuant to section 3923‑F.
19 Sec. 5. 7 MRSA §3923-A, sub-§4, as amended by PL 2013, c. 115, §10, is further
20 amended to read:
21 4. Late fees. An owner or keeper required to license a dog under section 3922,
22 subsection 1 or section 3923‑C 3932-B, subsection 1 and applying for a license for that dog
23 after January 31st shall pay to the municipal clerk, dog licensing agent or dog recorder a
24 late fee of $25 in addition to the annual license fee paid in accordance with subsection 1 or
25 2 and section 3923‑C, subsection 1. The clerk, dog licensing agent or dog recorder shall
26 deposit all late fees collected under this subsection into the municipality's animal welfare
27 account established in accordance with section 3945.'
28 Amend the bill in section 11 in §3932-B in subsection 2 in the last line (page 2, line 30
29 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "annually." the following: 'A humane agent may
30 conduct an inspection of a kennel in a municipality with an appointed animal control officer
31 under specific and extenuating circumstances as determined by the department by rule. If
32 a humane agent conducts an inspection pursuant to this subsection, the municipality shall
33 pay for the cost of the inspection.'
34 Amend the bill in section 11 in §3932-B in subsection 5 in the last line (page 3, line 3
35 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "department." the following: 'A humane agent
