COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 689, L.D. 1771
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, clarifies that kennel
55 licensees are not required to pay individual dog licensing fees.
6 The amendment clarifies that a humane agent with the Department of Agriculture,
7 Conservation and Forestry may conduct an inspection of a kennel in a municipality with
8 an appointed animal control officer under specific and extenuating circumstances as
9 determined by the department by rule. The amendment requires a municipality to pay for
10 the cost of an inspection if a humane agent conducts the inspection.
11 The amendment requires a kennel licensee to pay for a background check, which is
12 required to obtain a license. The amendment corrects a cross-reference in the Maine
13 Revised Statutes, Title 7, chapter 725 relating to municipal duties and officials' refusal or
14 neglect of duty.
15 The amendment requires the department to provide annual reports, no later than
16 January 15th in 2026, 2027 and 2028, to the joint standing committee of the Legislature
17 having jurisdiction over animal welfare matters on the transfer of the issuance of kennel
18 licenses from municipalities to the department. The joint standing committee may submit
19 legislation relating to the subject matter of the report to the Second Regular Session of the
20 132nd Legislature, to the 133rd Legislature in 2027 and to the Second Regular Session of
21 the 133rd Legislature.
